.TH "simple_write_to_buffer" 9 "simple_write_to_buffer" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
simple_write_to_buffer \- copy data from user space to the buffer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" simple_write_to_buffer
.BI "(void *to "  ","
.BI "size_t available "  ","
.BI "loff_t *ppos "  ","
.BI "const void __user *from "  ","
.BI "size_t count "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "to" 12
the buffer to write to
.IP "available" 12
the size of the buffer
.IP "ppos" 12
the current position in the buffer
.IP "from" 12
the user space buffer to read from
.IP "count" 12
the maximum number of bytes to read
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The \fBsimple_write_to_buffer\fP function reads up to \fIcount\fP bytes from the user
space address starting at \fIfrom\fP into the buffer \fIto\fP at offset \fIppos\fP.

On success, the number of bytes written is returned and the offset \fIppos\fP is
advanced by this number, or negative value is returned on error.
